ew York Times, Eve Kahn describes the use of maps outside&#8230;<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/decor/" rel="tag">装饰</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/new-york-times/" rel="tag">纽约时报</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> Eve Kahn 在《纽约时报》中描述了<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/09/style/maps-design.html?unlocked_article_code=1.ck0.vVYk.JyZT8FVzv8Xa&#038;smid=url-share">地图在查找方向之外的用途</a>：</p><blockquote><p>地图装饰可以帮助满足人类基本的定向需求。 “地图本质上是值得信赖的——它们让人们感到安全，”地图学者兼收藏家 PJ Mode 说，他将自己的藏品捐赠给康奈尔大学。他的主要关注点是“说服性制图”：旨在影响公众舆论的地图，例如在 1800 年代初期倡导废奴，或者在 1910 年代主张妇女选举权或好战。莫德先生喜欢引用作家兼飞行员贝丽尔·马卡姆 (Beryl Markham) 的设想，地图想对用户说的话：“密切关注我，不要怀疑我。 ……没有我，你会感到孤独和迷失。”</p></blockquote><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/decor/" rel="tag">装饰</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/new-york-times/" rel="tag">纽约时报</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 73614</post-id></item><item><title>常见的年龄差异，已婚夫妇</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/03/13/common-age-differences-married- Couples/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Wed, 13 Mar 2024 18:54:38 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Data Underload]]></category><category><![CDATA[age]]></category><category><![CDATA[marriage]]></category><category><![CDATA[relationships]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=73590 </guid><description><![CDATA[How common are wide age gaps between spouses? These are the age differences through the lens of the 2022 five-year American Community Survey.<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/age/" rel="tag">年龄</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/marriage/" rel="tag">婚姻</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/relationships/" rel="tag">人际关系</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> <a href="https://flowingdata.com/2024/03/13/common-age-differences-married-couples/"><img width="750" height="448" src="https://i0.wp.com/flowingda